# Turkish → ASCII-Latin transliteration rules (tr_lat.rules)
# References:
#   Arslan, A. (2016) “DeASCIIfication approach to handle diacritics in Turkish”, IP&M 52: 326-339, Table 1.
#   Torunoğlu, D. & Eryiğit, G. (2014) “A Cascaded Approach for Social Media Text Normalization of Turkish”, § 4.2.4.
# One-to-one, case-preserving fold of Turkish diacritic letters to plain Latin;
# all other ASCII letters map to themselves.

Ç > C ;  ç > c ;
Ğ > G ;  ğ > g ;
İ > I ;  i > i ;   # dotted I/i keep ASCII shape
I > I ;  ı > i ;   # dotless ı becomes ASCII i
Ö > O ;  ö > o ;
Ş > S ;  ş > s ;
Ü > U ;  ü > u ;

